name: ampere
definition: The base unit of electrical current in the International System of Units

name: ampere-hour
definition: A unit of electric charge equal to the charge transferred by a steady current of one ampere flowing for one hour

name: bar
definition: A unit of pressure equal to 100,000 Pa (or 100 kPa)

name: centimetre
definition: A unit of length in the International System of Units equal to one hundredth of a metre

name: cycles per minute
definition: A unit of frequency equal to the number of repeated cycles or other events occurring in one minute

name: degree
definition: The angle equal to one of 360 equally divided parts of a circle

name: degree Celsius
definition: The unit of temperature on the Celsius scale

name: degree per second
definition: The angular frequency that results in the angular displacement increasing by one degree every second

name: farad
definition: A unit of electrical capacitance (the ability of a body to store an electrical charge) equal to 1 coulomb per volt (C/V)

name: gram per second
definition: A unit of mass flow rate expressing one grams per second

name: hertz
definition: A unit of frequency equal to one event (or cycle) per second

name: inch
definition: A unit of length in the British imperial and the United States customary systems of measurement

name: joule
definition: A unit of energy equal to the amount of work done when a force of one newton displaces a mass through a distance of one metre in the direction of that force

name: kilogram
definition: The basic unit of mass originally intended to be equal to the mass of 1,000 cubic cm of water

name: kilometre
definition: A unit of length in the International System of Units equal to one thousand metres

name: kilometre per hour
definition: A unit of speed expressing kilometres travelled in one hour.

name: kilopascal
definition: A unit of pressure in the International System of Units expressing one thousand pascals

name: kilowatt hour
definition: A unit of energy equivalent to  one kilowatt of power extended for one hour

name: liter per hour
definition: A unit of volume flow rate expressing one liter per hour

name: metre
definition: The base unit of length in the International System of Units

name: metre per second
definition: A unit of both speed and velocity in the International System of Units expressing metres travelled in one second.

name: metre per second squared
definition: The unit of acceleration in the International System of Units expressing a change in velocity or speed expressed as metre per second per second

name: milliliter
definition: A unit of length expressing one thousandth of a metre

name: millimetre
definition: A unit of capacity expressing one thousandth of a liter

name: millisecond
definition: A unit of time expressing one thousandth of a secon

name: minute - time
definition: A unit of time equal to 60 seconds

name: newton-metre
definition: The torque resulting from a force of one newton applied perpendicularly to the end of a moment arm that is one metre long

name: ohm
definition: An electrical resistance between two points of a conductor when a constant potential difference of one volt  applied to these points produces a current of one ampere, the conductor not being the seat of any electromotive force

name: pascal
definition: The unit of pressure in the International System of Units

name: percent
definition: A number or ratio expressed as a fraction of 100

name: ratio
definition: An expression of how many times one number contains another

name: revolution per minute
definition: A unit of rotational speed (or rotational frequency) equivalent to 1/60 hertz

name: second
definition: The unit of time in the International System of Units

name: signed percent
definition: A number or ratio expressed as a fraction of 100 or -100

name: volt
definition: The unit of electric potential, electric potential difference (voltage), and electromotive force in the International System of Units

name: watt
definition: A unit of electrical power equal to one ampere under the pressure of one volt

name: watt hour
definition: A unit of energy equivalent to one watt of power expended for one hour
